    "body": "### Description\n\nOpening an Elixir script `.exs` (filetype is Elixir) outside of an Elixir project results in a crash of the [`expert` LSP](https://github.com/elixir-lang/expert):\n\n```\nError executing vim.schedule lua callback: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/client.lua:545: RPC[Error]\n code_name = InternalError, message = \"** (FunctionClauseError) no function clause matching in URI.parse/\n1\\\n    (elixir 1.19.5) lib/uri.ex:787: URI.parse(nil)\\\n    (xp_forge 0.1.0) lib/forge/document/path.ex:73: XPForge.Document.Path.from_uri/1\\\n    (xp_expert 0.1.0) lib/expert/state.ex:50: XPExpert.State.initialize/2\\\n    (xp_expert 0.1.0) lib/expert.ex:58: XPExpert.handle_request/2\\\n    (xp_gen_lsp 0.11.3) lib/gen_lsp.ex:390: anonymous fn/2 in XPGenLSP.loop/3\\\n    (xp_telemetry 1.3.0) /home/m.ottenklinger/.cache/yay/expert-git/src/expert/apps/expert/deps/telemetry\n/src/telemetry.erl:324: :xp_telemetry.span/3\\\n    (xp_gen_lsp 0.11.3) lib/gen_lsp.ex:389: anonymous fn/5 in XPGenLSP.loop/3\\\n    (xp_gen_lsp 0.11.3) lib/gen_lsp.ex:559: anonymous fn/4 in XPGenLSP.attempt/4\\\n\"\nstack traceback:\n        [C]: in function 'assert'\n        /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/client.lua:545: in function ''\n        vim/_editor.lua: in function <vim/_editor.lua:0>\n```\n\nThe root path provided in the [LSP configuration](https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/blob/44acfe887d4056f704ccc4f17513ed41c9e2b2e6/lsp/expert.lua#L20) seems to assume that an `mix.exs` is always present. That's not the case for plain Elixir scripts. In that case, the root path should probably be the script itself, or the directory holding that script.",
