            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "`on_dir(nil)` will activate \"single file mode\" (aka no workspace), so if this is not `nil` in the scenario you described, find out why and maybe send a PR: https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/blob/44acfe887d4056f704ccc4f17513ed41c9e2b2e6/lsp/expert.lua#L22\n\n> In that case, the root path should probably be the script itself, or the directory holding that script.\n\nok then `vim.fs.dirname(fname)` should achieve that. pr welcome...\n\nfor reference, https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/pull/4054 copied an approach from `lsp/elixirls.lua` cc @heywhy \n\nis `lsp/elixirls.lua` still active?",
